  "prompt": "Can bumble track your location even if you are not active? For example, if you are not currently using the application will it update where you are?",
  "response": "Bumble generally requires location access to provide location-based services, such as matching you with people nearby. This typically involves using your device's GPS or network-based location services. The app may periodically update your location even if you are not actively using it, depending on the permissions you've granted.\n\nHowever, Bumble's ability to track your location when the app is closed or not actively in use will depend on the settings you have configured on your device. On most smartphones, you can control whether an app has access to your location all the time, only when the app is in use, or never. For iOS devices, you can adjust these settings by going to Settings > Privacy > Location Services, while on Android devices, you can typically find these options under Settings > Location > App permissions.\n\nTo avoid location updates when you are not using the app, you can adjust the permissions to allow location access only while the app is in use.",
